GC.REV.GOTR.CN-fr.def: Grants and other revenue include grants from other foreign governments, international organizations, and other government units; interest; dividends; rent; requited, nonrepayable receipts for public purposes (such as fines, administrative fees, and entrepreneurial income from government owner­ship of property); and voluntary, unrequited, nonrepayable receipts other than grants.
GC.REV.GOTR.CN-fr.name: Grants and other revenue
GC.REV.GOTR.CN-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.REV.GOTR.ZS-fr.def: Grants and other revenue include grants from other foreign governments, international organizations, and other government units; interest; dividends; rent; requited, nonrepayable receipts for public purposes (such as fines, administrative fees, and entrepreneurial income from government owner­ship of property); and voluntary, unrequited, nonrepayable receipts other than grants.
GC.REV.GOTR.ZS-fr.name: Grants and other revenue
GC.REV.GOTR.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.REV.SOCL.CN-fr.def: Social contributions include social security contributions by employees, employers, and self-employed individuals, and other contributions whose source cannot be determined. They also include actual or imputed contributions to social insurance schemes operated by governments.
GC.REV.SOCL.CN-fr.name: Social contributions
GC.REV.SOCL.CN-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.REV.SOCL.ZS-fr.def: Social contributions include social security contributions by employees, employers, and self-employed individuals, and other contributions whose source cannot be determined. They also include actual or imputed contributions to social insurance schemes operated by governments.
GC.REV.SOCL.ZS-fr.name: Social contributions
GC.REV.SOCL.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.REV.XGRT.CN-fr.def: Revenue is cash receipts from taxes, social contributions, and other revenues such as fines, fees, rent, and income from property or sales. Grants are also considered as revenue but are excluded here.
GC.REV.XGRT.CN-fr.name: Revenue
GC.REV.XGRT.CN-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.REV.XGRT.GD.ZS-fr.def: Revenue is cash receipts from taxes, social contributions, and other revenues such as fines, fees, rent, and income from property or sales. Grants are also considered as revenue but are excluded here.
GC.REV.XGRT.GD.ZS-fr.name: Revenue
GC.REV.XGRT.GD.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files, and World Bank and OECD GDP estimates.

GC.TAX.EXPT.CN-fr.def: Taxes on exports are all levies on goods being transported out of the country or services being delivered to nonresidents by residents. Rebates on exported goods that are repayments of previously paid general consumption taxes, excise taxes, or import duties are deducted from the gross amounts receivable from these taxes, not from amounts receivable from export taxes.
GC.TAX.EXPT.CN-fr.name: Taxes on exports
GC.TAX.EXPT.CN-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.EXPT.ZS-fr.def: Taxes on exports are all levies on goods being transported out of the country or services being delivered to nonresidents by residents. Rebates on exported goods that are repayments of previously paid general consumption taxes, excise taxes, or import duties are deducted from the gross amounts receivable from these taxes, not from amounts receivable from export taxes.
GC.TAX.EXPT.ZS-fr.name: Taxes on exports
GC.TAX.EXPT.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.GSRV.CN-fr.def: Taxes on goods and services include general sales and turnover or value added taxes, selective excises on goods, selective taxes on services, taxes on the use of goods or property, taxes on extraction and production of minerals, and profits of fiscal monopolies.
GC.TAX.GSRV.CN-fr.name: Taxes on goods and services
GC.TAX.GSRV.CN-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.GSRV.RV.ZS-fr.def: Taxes on goods and services include general sales and turnover or value added taxes, selective excises on goods, selective taxes on services, taxes on the use of goods or property, taxes on extraction and production of minerals, and profits of fiscal monopolies.
GC.TAX.GSRV.RV.ZS-fr.name: Taxes on goods and services
GC.TAX.GSRV.RV.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.GSRV.VA.ZS-fr.def: Taxes on goods and services include general sales and turnover or value added taxes, selective excises on goods, selective taxes on services, taxes on the use of goods or property, taxes on extraction and production of minerals, and profits of fiscal monopolies.
GC.TAX.GSRV.VA.ZS-fr.name: Taxes on goods and services
GC.TAX.GSRV.VA.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files, and World Bank and OECD value added estimates.
GC.TAX.GSRV.VA.ZS-fr.dim: % value added of industry and services
GC.TAX.GSRV.VA.ZS-fr.units: % value added of industry and services

GC.TAX.IMPT.CN-fr.def: Customs and other import duties are all levies collected on goods that are entering the country or services delivered by nonresidents to residents. They include levies imposed for revenue or protection purposes and determined on a specific or ad valorem basis as long as they are restricted to imported goods or services.
GC.TAX.IMPT.CN-fr.name: Customs and other import duties
GC.TAX.IMPT.CN-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.IMPT.ZS-fr.def: Customs and other import duties are all levies collected on goods that are entering the country or services delivered by nonresidents to residents. They include levies imposed for revenue or protection purposes and determined on a specific or ad valorem basis as long as they are restricted to imported goods or services.
GC.TAX.IMPT.ZS-fr.name: Customs and other import duties
GC.TAX.IMPT.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.INTT.CN-fr.def: Taxes on international trade include import duties, export duties, profits of export or import monopolies, exchange profits, and exchange taxes.
GC.TAX.INTT.CN-fr.name: Taxes on international trade
GC.TAX.INTT.CN-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.INTT.RV.ZS-fr.def: Taxes on international trade include import duties, export duties, profits of export or import monopolies, exchange profits, and exchange taxes.
GC.TAX.INTT.RV.ZS-fr.name: Taxes on international trade
GC.TAX.INTT.RV.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.OTHR.CN-fr.def: Other taxes include employer payroll or labor taxes, taxes on property, and taxes not allocable to other categories, such as penalties for late payment or nonpayment of taxes.
GC.TAX.OTHR.CN-fr.name: Other taxes
GC.TAX.OTHR.CN-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.OTHR.RV.ZS-fr.def: Other taxes include employer payroll or labor taxes, taxes on property, and taxes not allocable to other categories, such as penalties for late payment or nonpayment of taxes.
GC.TAX.OTHR.RV.ZS-fr.name: Other taxes
GC.TAX.OTHR.RV.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.TOTL.CN-fr.def: Tax revenue refers to compulsory transfers to the central government for public purposes. Certain compulsory transfers such as fines, penalties, and most social security contributions are excluded. Refunds and corrections of erroneously collected tax revenue are treated as negative revenue.
GC.TAX.TOTL.CN-fr.name: Tax revenue
GC.TAX.TOTL.CN-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.TOTL.GD.ZS-fr.def: Tax revenue refers to compulsory transfers to the central government for public purposes. Certain compulsory transfers such as fines, penalties, and most social security contributions are excluded. Refunds and corrections of erroneously collected tax revenue are treated as negative revenue.
GC.TAX.TOTL.GD.ZS-fr.name: Tax revenue
GC.TAX.TOTL.GD.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files, and World Bank and OECD GDP estimates.

GC.TAX.YPKG.CN-fr.def: Taxes on income, profits, and capital gains are levied on the actual or presumptive net income of individuals, on the profits of corporations and enterprises, and on capital gains, whether realized or not, on land, securities, and other assets. Intragovernmental payments are eliminated in consolidation.
GC.TAX.YPKG.CN-fr.name: Taxes on income
GC.TAX.YPKG.CN-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.YPKG.RV.ZS-fr.def: Taxes on income, profits, and capital gains are levied on the actual or presumptive net income of individuals, on the profits of corporations and enterprises, and on capital gains, whether realized or not, on land, securities, and other assets. Intragovernmental payments are eliminated in consolidation.
GC.TAX.YPKG.RV.ZS-fr.name: Taxes on income
GC.TAX.YPKG.RV.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.

GC.TAX.YPKG.ZS-fr.def: Taxes on income, profits, and capital gains are levied on the actual or presumptive net income of individuals, on the profits of corporations and enterprises, and on capital gains, whether realized or not, on land, securities, and other assets. Intragovernmental payments are eliminated in consolidation.
GC.TAX.YPKG.ZS-fr.name: Taxes on income
GC.TAX.YPKG.ZS-fr.source: International Monetary Fund, Government Finance Statistics Yearbook and data files.
